properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 5:27AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
A developing low pressure will rapidly intensify as it lifts out
of the north Pacific on Tuesday. This very powerful weather
system will move into the Gulf of Alaska by Tuesday night and then
move inland over the Kenai Peninsula by Wednesday afternoon.

As the associated weather front moves over the Gulf of Alaska
Tuesday, east winds will increase to storm force over the eastern
side of the gulf and spread into the northern gulf through
Tuesday night. Gale force southwest winds will persist into
Wednesday behind the front. Wave heights will build as the low
moves north and range from 25 to 35 feet by Wednesday morning.
Marine travel will be very hazardous over the Gulf of Alaska
through this event.

Winds over the coastal land areas will increase Tuesday night with
gusts near 50 mph or higher. Other areas over the inner channels
will also see gusty winds through Tuesday night and Wednesday with
gusts from 40 to 50 mph. Be sure to secure loose objects prior to
Tuesday night. Also be prepared for power outages, travel delays
and other impacts from this event.

NWSheadline: SIGNIFICANT LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM TO IMPACT GULF OF ALASKA AND SOUTHEAST ALASKA TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY
